BLUETONGUE, SHEEP - ITALY (SARDINIA): OIE REPORT
************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
Date: 1 Sep 2000
From: Peter Cowen <Peter_Cowen@ncsu.edu>
Source: OIE Disease Information No. 13 Vol 34
<http://www.oie.int/Info/A_info.htm>

BLUETONGUE IN ITALY
Emergency report
Text of a fax received on 31 Aug 2000 from Dr Romano Marabelli, Director
General of Veterinary Services, Ministry of Public Health, Rome:
Report date: 31 Aug 2000.
Nature of diagnosis: clinical and laboratory.
Date of initial detection of animal health incident: 18 Aug 2000.
Outbreaks:
Location: Sardinia island
No. of outbreaks: 71
Description of affected population: Sardinian sheep (adults and lambs).
Total number of animals in the outbreaks:
species/ susceptible/ cases/ deaths/ destroyed/ slaughtered
ovi/ 17 822/ 755/ 190/ 0/ 0
Diagnosis:
A. Laboratory where diagnosis was made: Experimental Animal Disease Control
Institute, Teramo.
B. Diagnostic tests used: serological tests (ELISA(1) - agar gel
immunodiffusion), virus isolation.
Control measures during reporting period: control of insect vectors;
control of animal movement inside the country; modified stamping out and
screening.
(1) ELISA: enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay
